Description:
    Toggle between email and SMS authentication methods in your Rails application.
    This generator switches the authentication system, updates routes, runs migrations,
    and clears all existing users.

Example:
    bin/rails generate auth_toggle sms
    bin/rails generate auth_toggle email
    bin/rails generate auth_toggle --status

    This will:
        - Update config/application.rb with the new authentication method
        - Rewrite config/routes.rb with appropriate controller mappings
        - Run database migration to update user table schema
        - Clear all existing users from the database
        - Display instructions for next steps

Options:
    --status    Show current authentication method without making changes

Authentication Methods:
    email       Email/password authentication with registration and password reset
    sms         SMS verification authentication using phone numbers

Files Created/Modified:
    config/application.rb   - Authentication method configuration
    config/routes.rb        - Route mappings for chosen authentication
    db/migrate/*           - Migration to update user table schema

Note:
    - All existing users will be cleared when switching authentication methods
    - Server restart required after switching for configuration changes to take effect
    - SMS authentication uses mocked Twilio service for development (codes: 1234, 0000)
